<font color="#FF0000">DAMN IT ED, IT IS SANDLES.</font><br>
<tt>Thu Aug 28 23:09:21 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Damn it boy, Edward Ramon, how many times I got to tell you that it is SANDLES, not tennis shoes.<br><br>
You know, I always got a laugh when the likes of Bob B-1 Dornan, Congressmen of Orange County, used to call us &quot;unwashed commie hippie pinko protestors&quot; or the like. Hell, I always took a shower every day. Esp. with all that long hair (which the babes loved), Even my mother would brush my long hair and say how beautiful it was. Better than most girls she would say. (man that sounds bizarre now, esp that she is long dead and gone).  But Ed, come on, no tennis shoes, even thou Orange County is the home of Vans, and Rainbow thongs, it still is hippie made sandles that rule. The kind you use when you drive your chevy and stuff out the fords. The kind you use when you are running from the cops after a war protest. The kind you use when you don't want to slip cause a platoon of marines, who are drunk, is chasing you after one of those &quot;peace&quot; demostrations, and they don't exactly mean they want to play cards. They want to give you a haircut and more.  So &quot;feats don't fail me now&quot; if you catch my drift. Leather sandles, with tight buckles, was the hippie equilvent of the G.I. Combat boot. Both designed with a purpose in mind.  Good Traction and good running. In in our case, good escape.  Sure Nikes would have been better, if they had been invented back then, but politically incorrect.  Mexican sandles were so so. Hippie sandles, made by some zoned out space cadet, if not yourself, was the appropriate attire for a demostration. Don't forget the tie die t shirt and bell bottom jeans too.  Damn, the protestors had just as much uniform as you vets did.  Shhhhh, don't tell anyone.<br><br>
Meamwhile, I will crawl into my bed, with my Lions Drag Strip Trophy sitting next to the bed, where I trophied and beat the top dog ford, running B stock in 1963, turned 88 in 15.85.  (hot dog!!).  The other guy paniced and missed his shift, but I had him anyway.  I still have that trophie, and I still dust it weekly.  Chevys rule, and as for the rest, protestors and veterans, we all check each others six for bad guys.   Time for this old coot to crash it in. I got to be awake and in the office tomorrow and act like I care.
